      vps4
     </em>
     Δ cells (
     <xref ref-type="bibr">
      Katzmann et al, 2001
     </xref>
     ) (
     <xref ref-type="fig">
      Figure 4C
     </xref>
     ), which provides a convenient diagnostic for the determinants of endosomal localization. The mean number of wild-type Vps23-containing puncta was 1.4 per cell based on blind counting.
     <em>
      VPS23
     </em>
     <sup>
      <em>
       W16A
      </em>
     </sup>
     (
     <xref ref-type="fig">
      Figure 4D
     </xref>
     ), but not
     <em>
      VPS23
     </em>
     , was cytosolic in
     <em>
      vps4
     </em>
     Δ
     <em>
      vps23
     </em>
     Δcells, indicating an impairment of endosomal localization in the
     <em>
      VPS23
     </em>
     <sup>
      <em>
       W16A
      </em>
     </sup>
     form of ESCRT-I. The mean number of Vps23
     <sup>
